> Why are we adding it to each suite manually?

Setting some values automatically in keywords saves space in suites, but makes it harder for humans to see what the values are. In the past, we had some mis-configurations which took a long time to detect.
As time goes, we tend do make values more explicit, e.g. setting ${overhead} in every suite even if in 95% of those it is zero.
